plugin-glassnav-glass
=====================

A port of GlassNav into GlassHole's plugin system. GPL-3.0-or-later
(see LICENSE).

Original work
-------------

* **GlassNav** by **CatotheCat11**
  Repository: https://github.com/CatotheCat11/GlassNav
  License: GPL-3.0-or-later

  The Java/Kotlin source files under `com.cato.glassnav`
  (MainActivity, SearchActivity, RouteActivity, Utils, CustomTrust,
  HttpsUtils, OsmMvtTileSource, KotlinUtils) are imported essentially
  verbatim from CatotheCat11's repository. The original package
  structure, class names and the `com.cato.glassnav` namespace are
  preserved so improvements can flow back upstream cleanly.

  The drawables (turn arrows, location/marker textures, mode icons,
  bookmark/search/close glyphs), the VTM dark theme XML, the layout
  (`mapviewer.xml`) and the values resources (colors, dimens,
  strings, themes) are likewise imported from the upstream
  repository.

GlassHole integration work
--------------------------

* **Ben Harlett** (benharlett@gmail.com)

  - `BluetoothMapsService.java` gutted to a compatibility shim — the
    upstream RFCOMM transport is replaced by `GlassNavPluginService`,
    which receives `DEST` / `LOC` / `REQ_GPS_START` messages over
    GlassHole's existing BT bridge instead.
  - `GlassNavPluginService.kt` — the new transport service. Buffers
    incoming messages until `MainActivity` registers its listener
    (cold-start race) and exposes the dynamic-config flow via
    `PluginConfigHandler` so the plugin gets a settings gear on the
    phone-side Plugins screen.
  - `plugin_schema.json` — settings UI definition (keep-screen-on,
    distance units, default route mode, ETA format, speedometer
    mode + position).
  - Manifest re-targeted to GlassHole's plugin discovery
    (`com.glasshole.plugin.GLASS_PLUGIN` action + ID/NAME/
    DESCRIPTION/SCHEMA meta-data).
  - Multi-region offline-map picker — `MainActivity.pickBestOfflineMap`
    scans `/sdcard/glasshole/maps/*.map` and picks the file whose
    bbox contains the current GPS position (smallest-bbox-wins).
    The legacy `/sdcard/Map.map` slot still works as a fallback.
  - Map rotation simplified to always head-up regardless of travel
    mode; auto-fallback to driving when Valhalla rejects walk/cycle
    with `DistanceExceeded`; ETA formatter handles long routes
    cleanly.

Vendored dependencies (see apps/lib/)
-------------------------------------

* **maplibre-navigation-core** (apps/lib/maplibre-navigation-core/)
  — a fork of the MapLibre Navigation SDK with KitKat-compatibility
  patches, imported from CatotheCat11/GlassNav.
  MIT-licensed. © Kurviger (2024), MapLibre (2021), Flitsmeister
  (2019). Includes shim classes under
  `org.maplibre.geojson.{model,turf,utils}` that bridge nav-core's
  expected Kotlin-port API to the Java maplibre-gl 6.0.1 artifacts
  we can actually load on our Kotlin 1.9 toolchain — those shims
  are MIT-by-extension since they're part of the same module.

* **glass-gdk-stubs** (apps/lib/glass-gdk-stubs/) — compile-only
  Google Glass Development Kit class shapes (Sounds, Gesture,
  GestureDetector, CardBuilder, CardScrollView, CardScrollAdapter).
  Real implementations come from the Glass OS at runtime.
  Apache-2.0.

External dependencies (resolved by Gradle)
------------------------------------------

* **VTM** 0.27.0 — vector map renderer, © Mapsforge contributors.
  LGPL-3.0. https://github.com/mapsforge/vtm
* **Mapsforge** 0.27.0 — raster + offline `.map` rendering.
  LGPL-3.0. https://github.com/mapsforge/mapsforge
* **OpenPrism** 1.2.0 — Glass UI library (bundles the GDK widget
  classes). © CatotheCat11. Apache-2.0.
  https://github.com/CatotheCat11/OpenPrism
* **MapLibre GeoJSON / Turf** 6.0.1 — geometry primitives.
  Apache-2.0. https://github.com/maplibre/maplibre-java
* **Conscrypt** 2.5.3 — modern TLS on KitKat. Apache-2.0.
  https://github.com/google/conscrypt
* **OkHttp** 3.12.12 + **Okio** 3.6.0 — Apache-2.0, © Square Inc.
* **AndroidSVG** 1.4 — Apache-2.0.
* **Mapbox Vector Tile** 4.0.6 — Apache-2.0.
* **JTS Core** 1.20.0 — EPL-2.0 + EDL-1.0 (BSD-3-Clause).
  https://github.com/locationtech/jts
* **Protobuf Java** 3.24.2 — BSD-3-Clause, © Google LLC.
* **kotlinx-serialization-json** 1.6.3, **kotlinx-coroutines-core**
  1.7.3 — Apache-2.0, © JetBrains s.r.o.

Map data
--------

Online tile fetches use the OpenStreetMap US tile service. Offline
`.map` files are published by mapsforge.org from OpenStreetMap data.

OpenStreetMap data is licensed under the **Open Database License**
(ODbL) 1.0 — © OpenStreetMap contributors,
https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright

Routing
-------

Turn-by-turn directions are fetched from the public Valhalla server
at https://valhalla1.openstreetmap.de (Apache-2.0). Place search is
Nominatim at https://nominatim.openstreetmap.org (BSD/Public Domain).
Both are OpenStreetMap-community-run services; respect their
fair-use policies if forking.
